t]) -> int:\n        max_count = 0\n        current_count = 0\n        \n        for num in nums:\n            if num == 1:\n                current_count += 1\n                max_count = max(max_count, current_count)\n            else:\n                current_count = 0\n        \n        return max_count\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the list `nums`, keeping track of the current streak of consecutive 1's with `current_count`. It updates `max_count` whenever `current_count` exceeds it. When a 0 is encountered, `current_count` is reset to 0. The function finally returns `max_count`, which holds the maximum number of consecutive 1's found in the array.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}